## Findings

No raster, vector, or CSS-background image assets exist anywhere in this demo. Every visual element is CSS/HTML/emoji-driven. The demo's 12 files (index.html, styles.css, app.js, db.js, llm-router.js, mock-integrations.js, ui/shell.js, ui/intel-brief.js, ui/output-queue.js, engines/authority.js, engines/newsletter.js, engines/knowledge.js) contain zero `<img>` tags, zero `background-image` declarations, and zero `url()` references pointing to image assets.

The `screenshot: null` in workSamples.js is correct: media-capture has not run yet and is expected to produce `public/work-samples/real-estate-intelligence-center.png`.

No image problems to report.

